<subSubSection pageNumber="529" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="529">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Note:</emphasis>
Stearn (in Geck &amp; Pressler, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Festschr. Claus Nissen</emphasis>
: 639. 1974) discussed this name, which was published in the 1759 reprint of the dissertation 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">
<volumeTitle pageNumber="529">Flora Monspeliensis</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’" pageNumber="529">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
name is validated solely by a reference to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Magnol’s" pageNumber="529">Magnol's</normalizedToken>
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="529">Botanicum Monspeliense</emphasis>
: 109. 1676, the text of which Stearn reproduces, along with a plate (
<normalizedToken originalValue="Magnol’s" pageNumber="529">Magnol's</normalizedToken>
t. 8; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Stearn’s" pageNumber="529">Stearn's</normalizedToken>
f. 3). Under Art. 7.7, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’" pageNumber="529">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
binomial must be typified &quot;by an element selected from the context of the validating description or diagnosis&quot;, and the type choice made by Guittonneau of Magnol material in MPU is therefore accepted here.
</paragraph>
